ca.fwe.units
Class BaseUnit

java.lang.Object
  ca.fwe.units.BaseUnit

public class BaseUnit
extends java.lang.Object

Author:
Dewey Dunnington A class containing units of the 7 base unit types (as defined by SI), defining them in terms of their SI unit and Dimension. These units are not used on their own, but should be used as components in a Unit.

BaseUnit

public BaseUnit(BaseUnit.Dimension base,
                java.lang.String name,
                java.lang.String abbreviation,
                double ratio,
                double offset)
Parameters:
base - dimension associated with this BaseUnit
name - long form name
abbreviation - unique abbreviation for the BaseUnit. Must be unique, as it is used to store units.
ratio - ratio between the SI unit and this unit (i.e. what you would multiply a value in this unit to get the value in SI units)
offset - used to accommodate degrees celcius and farenheight, but not implemented in the Unit class.
